// vm-ready
// Regression test: accessing a variable from an outer block scope inside a list comprehension
// guard used to panic with "slot not found in any scope within function".
//
// The bug was in get_type's upvalue navigation: iteration scopes have creates_environment=true
// (needed so closures capture the right iteration variable), but don't reset slot numbering like
// function scopes do. This caused get_type to overshoot by one environment boundary when the
// current scope was the iteration scope itself, landing at the function scope instead of the
// outer block scope that owns the variable.
//
// The while loop is load-bearing: it introduces a block scope between the function scope and the
// iteration scope, which is what triggers the off-by-one in scope traversal.
let i = 0;
while i < 1 {
    let target = 5;
    let result = [x for x in 0..10, if x == target];
    assert_eq(result, [5]);
    i += 1;
}
